\begin{align} \frac{x}{32} &= \left( \frac{3.9}{48} \right) (1 + 0.25) \end{align}
Solving for $x$:
\begin{align} x &= \left( \frac{3.9}{48} \right) (1.25) (32)\\ &= \frac{3.9 \times 1.25 \times 32}{48} \\ &= 3.9 \times 1.25 \\ &= 4.875 \end{align}

